library->math

primer, ch.16/modern, lvl.1.8.2

defined in [math.h] and [tgmath.h] (latter simpler)
    - double ceil(double x) returns the smallest integral value not less than x
    - double fabs(double x) returns the absolute value of x
    - double floor(double x) returns the largest integral value not greater than x
    - ...
    - by default, each func expects arg(s) of type double and return a double-val
        - for each func, versions for float and long also provided (f- or l-suffix)

EXAMPLE
#include <math.h>
#include <stdio.h>
printf("%.2f\n", fabsf(4.5f));// 4.50
printf("%.2Lf\n", floorl(4.5l)); // 4.00
printf("%.2f\n", ceil(4.5)); // 5.00
